fields.name: LogRetention
fields.description: LogRetention is the option to set the log retention policy for the CloudWatch Log Group. Defaults to Never Expire if not specified or set to 0 Possible values are 1, 3, 5, 7, 14, 30, 60, 90, 120, 150, 180, 365, 400, 545, 731, 1827, 2192, 2557, 2922, 3288, or 3653

fields.name: LogGroupName

fields.name: RetainInitialValueOfDeltaMetric
fields.description: RetainInitialValueOfDeltaMetric is the flag to signal that the initial value of a metric is a valid datapoint. The default behavior is that the first value occurrence of a metric is set as the baseline for the calculation of the delta to the next occurrence. With this flag set to true the exporter will instead use this first value as the initial delta value. This is especially useful when handling low frequency metrics.

fields.name: DimensionRollupOption
fields.description: DimensionRollupOption is the option for metrics dimension rollup. Three options are available, default option is "ZeroAndSingleDimensionRollup". "ZeroAndSingleDimensionRollup" - Enable both zero dimension rollup and single dimension rollup "SingleDimensionRollupOnly" - Enable single dimension rollup "NoDimensionRollup" - No dimension rollup (only keep original metrics which contain all dimensions)

fields.name: Endpoint

fields.name: Username
fields.description: Username is the authentication username.

fields.name: Password
fields.description: Password is the authentication password.

fields.name: Database
fields.description: Database is the database name to export.

fields.name: ConnectionParams
fields.description: ConnectionParams is the extra connection parameters with map format. for example compression/dial_timeout

fields.name: LogsTableName
fields.description: LogsTableName is the table name for logs. default is `otel_logs`.

fields.name: TracesTableName
fields.description: TracesTableName is the table name for traces. default is `otel_traces`.

fields.name: MetricsTableName
fields.description: MetricsTableName is the table name for metrics. default is `otel_metrics`. Deprecated: MetricsTableName exists for historical compatibility and should not be used. To set the metrics tables name, use the MetricsTables parameter instead.

fields.name: TTL
fields.description: TTL is The data time-to-live example 30m, 48h. 0 means no ttl.

fields.name: TableEngine
fields.description: TableEngine is the table engine to use. default is `MergeTree()`.

fields.name: ClusterName
fields.description: ClusterName if set will append `ON CLUSTER` with the provided name when creating tables.

fields.name: CreateSchema
fields.description: CreateSchema if set to true will run the DDL for creating the database and tables. default is true.

fields.name: Compress
fields.description: Compress controls the compression algorithm. Valid options: `none` (disabled), `zstd`, `lz4` (default), `gzip`, `deflate`, `br`, `true` (lz4).

fields.name: AsyncInsert
fields.description: AsyncInsert if true will enable async inserts. Default is `true`. Ignored if async inserts are configured in the `endpoint` or `connection_params`. Async inserts may still be overridden server-side.

fields.name: MetricsTables
fields.description: MetricsTables defines the table names for metric types.

fields.description: CreateSchema is whether databases and tables are created automatically.

fields.description: Data older than these days will be deleted; ignored if create_schema is false. If set to 0, historical data will not be deleted.

fields.description: The number of days in the history partition that was created when the table was created; ignored if create_schema is false. If history_days is not 0, create_history_days needs to be less than or equal to history_days.

fields.name: LogProgressInterval

fields.name: timeLocation

name: elasticsearchexporter
description: This exporter supports sending logs, metrics, traces and profiles to [Elasticsearch](https://www.elastic.co/elasticsearch).

fields.name: Endpoints
fields.description: Endpoints holds the Elasticsearch URLs the exporter should send events to. This setting is required if CloudID is not set and if the ELASTICSEARCH_URL environment variable is not set.

fields.name: CloudID
fields.description: CloudID holds the cloud ID to identify the Elastic Cloud cluster to send events to. https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/cloud/current/ec-cloud-id.html This setting is required if no URL is configured.

fields.name: NumWorkers
fields.description: NumWorkers configures the number of workers publishing bulk requests.

fields.name: LogsIndex
fields.description: LogsIndex configures the static index used for document routing for logs. It should be empty if dynamic document routing is preferred.

fields.name: MetricsIndex
fields.description: MetricsIndex configures the static index used for document routing for metrics. It should be empty if dynamic document routing is preferred.

fields.name: TracesIndex
fields.description: TracesIndex configures the static index used for document routing for metrics. It should be empty if dynamic document routing is preferred.

fields.name: LogsDynamicID
fields.description: LogsDynamicID configures whether log record attribute `elasticsearch.document_id` is set as the document ID in ES.

fields.name: LogsDynamicPipeline
fields.description: LogsDynamicPipeline configures whether log record attribute `elasticsearch.document_pipeline` is set as the document ingest pipeline for ES.

fields.name: Pipeline
fields.description: Pipeline configures the ingest node pipeline name that should be used to process the events. https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/ingest.html

fields.name: Batcher
fields.description: Batcher holds configuration for batching requests based on timeout and size-based thresholds. Batcher is unused by default, in which case Flush will be used. If Batcher.Enabled is non-nil (i.e. batcher::enabled is specified), then the Flush will be ignored even if Batcher.Enabled is false.

fields.name: FlushInterval

fields.name: GroupBy

fields.name: LogRecordDimensions
fields.description: LogRecordDimensions are log record attributes to be used as line protocol tags. These are always included as tags, if available: - trace ID - span ID The default values: - service.name Other common attributes can be found here: - https://opentelemetry.io/docs/specs/semconv/ When using InfluxDB for both logs and traces, be certain that log_record_dimensions matches the tracing span_dimensions value.

fields.description: APIURL is the destination to where SignalFx metadata will be sent. This value takes precedence over the value of Realm

fields.name: APITLSSettings
fields.description: api_tls needs to be set if the exporter's APIURL is pointing to a httpforwarder extension with TLS enabled and using a self-signed certificate where its CA is not loaded in the system cert pool.

fields.name: LogDataPoints
fields.description: Whether to log datapoints dispatched to Splunk Observability Cloud

fields.name: LogDimensionUpdates
fields.description: Whether to log dimension updates being sent to SignalFx.

fields.name: DimensionClient
fields.description: Dimension update client configuration used for metadata updates.

fields.name: DeltaTranslationTTL
fields.description: DeltaTranslationTTL specifies in seconds the max duration to keep the most recent datapoint for any `delta_metric` specified in TranslationRules. Default is 3600s.

fields.name: SyncHostMetadata
fields.description: SyncHostMetadata defines if the exporter should scrape host metadata and sends it as property updates to SignalFx backend. IMPORTANT: Host metadata synchronization relies on `resourcedetection` processor. If this option is enabled make sure that `resourcedetection` processor is enabled in the pipeline with one of the cloud provider detectors or environment variable detector setting a unique value to `host.name` attribute within your k8s cluster. Also keep override And keep `override=true` in resourcedetection config.

fields.name: ExcludeMetrics
fields.description: ExcludeMetrics defines dpfilter.MetricFilters that will determine metrics to be excluded from sending to SignalFx backend. If translations enabled with TranslationRules options, the exclusion will be applied on translated metrics.

fields.name: IncludeMetrics
fields.description: IncludeMetrics defines dpfilter.MetricFilters to override exclusion any of metric. This option can be used to included metrics that are otherwise dropped by default. See ./translation/default_metrics.go for a list of metrics that are dropped by default.

fields.name: ExcludeProperties
fields.description: ExcludeProperties defines dpfilter.PropertyFilters to prevent inclusion of properties to include with dimension updates to the SignalFx backend.

fields.name: Correlation
fields.description: Correlation configuration for syncing traces service and environment to metrics.

fields.name: NonAlphanumericDimensionChars
fields.description: NonAlphanumericDimensionChars is a list of allowable characters, in addition to alphanumeric ones, to be used in a dimension key.

fields.name: DropHistogramBuckets
fields.description: Whether to drop histogram bucket metrics dispatched to Splunk Observability. Default value is set to false.

fields.name: SendOTLPHistograms
fields.description: Whether to send histogram metrics in OTLP format to Splunk Observability. Default value is set to false.

name: splunkhecexporter
description: ## Configuration

fields.name: BatcherConfig
fields.description: Experimental: This configuration is at the early stage of development and may change without backward compatibility until https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-collector/issues/8122 is resolved.

fields.name: LogDataEnabled
fields.description: LogDataEnabled can be used to disable sending logs by the exporter.

fields.name: ProfilingDataEnabled
fields.description: ProfilingDataEnabled can be used to disable sending profiling data by the exporter.

fields.name: Token
fields.description: HEC Token is the authentication token provided by Splunk: https://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/latest/Data/UsetheHTTPEventCollector.

fields.name: Source
fields.description: Optional Splunk source: https://docs.splunk.com/Splexicon:Source. Sources identify the incoming data.

fields.name: SourceType
fields.description: Optional Splunk source type: https://docs.splunk.com/Splexicon:Sourcetype.

fields.name: Index
fields.description: Splunk index, optional name of the Splunk index.

fields.name: DisableCompression
fields.description: Disable GZip compression. Defaults to false.

fields.name: MaxContentLengthLogs
fields.description: Maximum log payload size in bytes. Default value is 2097152 bytes (2MiB). Maximum allowed value is 838860800 (~ 800 MB).

fields.name: MaxContentLengthMetrics
fields.description: Maximum metric payload size in bytes. Default value is 2097152 bytes (2MiB). Maximum allowed value is 838860800 (~ 800 MB).

fields.name: MaxContentLengthTraces
fields.description: Maximum trace payload size in bytes. Default value is 2097152 bytes (2MiB). Maximum allowed value is 838860800 (~ 800 MB).

fields.name: MaxEventSize
fields.description: Maximum payload size, raw uncompressed. Default value is 5242880 bytes (5MiB). Maximum allowed value is 838860800 (~ 800 MB).

fields.name: SplunkAppName
fields.description: App name is used to track telemetry information for Splunk App's using HEC by App name. Defaults to "OpenTelemetry Collector Contrib".

fields.name: SplunkAppVersion
fields.description: App version is used to track telemetry information for Splunk App's using HEC by App version. Defaults to the current OpenTelemetry Collector Contrib build version.

fields.name: OtelAttrsToHec
fields.description: OtelAttrsToHec creates a mapping from attributes to HEC specific metadata: source, sourcetype, index and host.

fields.name: HecToOtelAttrs
fields.description: HecToOtelAttrs creates a mapping from attributes to HEC specific metadata: source, sourcetype, index and host. Deprecated: [v0.113.0] Use OtelAttrsToHec instead.

fields.name: HecFields
fields.description: HecFields creates a mapping from attributes to HEC fields.

fields.name: HealthPath
fields.description: HealthPath for health API, default is '/services/collector/health'

fields.name: HecHealthCheckEnabled
fields.description: HecHealthCheckEnabled can be used to verify Splunk HEC health on exporter's startup

fields.name: ExportRaw
fields.description: ExportRaw to send only the log's body, targeting a Splunk HEC raw endpoint.

fields.name: UseMultiMetricFormat
fields.description: UseMultiMetricFormat combines metric events to save space during ingestion.

fields.name: Heartbeat
fields.description: Heartbeat is the configuration to enable heartbeat

fields.name: Telemetry
fields.description: Telemetry is the configuration for splunk hec exporter telemetry

name: sumologicexporter
description: ## Migration to new architecture

fields.name: CompressEncoding
fields.description: Compression encoding format, either empty string, gzip or deflate (default gzip) Empty string means no compression NOTE: CompressEncoding is deprecated and will be removed in an upcoming release

fields.name: MaxRequestBodySize
fields.description: Max HTTP request body size in bytes before compression (if applied). By default 1MB is recommended.

fields.name: LogFormat
fields.description: Logs related configuration Format to post logs into Sumo. (default json) * text - Logs will appear in Sumo Logic in text format. * json - Logs will appear in Sumo Logic in json format. * otlp - Logs will be send in otlp format and will appear in Sumo Logic: * in json format if record level attributes exists * in text format in case of no level attributes See Sumo Logic documentation for more details: https://help.sumologic.com/docs/send-data/opentelemetry-collector/data-source-configurations/mapping-records-resources/

fields.name: MetricFormat
fields.description: Metrics related configuration The format of metrics you will be sending, either otlp or prometheus (Default is otlp)

fields.name: DecomposeOtlpHistograms
fields.description: Decompose OTLP Histograms into individual metrics, similar to how they're represented in Prometheus format

fields.name: Client
fields.description: Sumo specific options Name of the client

fields.name: StickySessionEnabled
fields.description: StickySessionEnabled defines if sticky session support is enable. By default this is false.

name: syslogexporter
description: The Syslog exporter sends logs in [syslog][syslog_wikipedia] format to a remote syslog server.

fields.name: Endpoint
fields.description: Syslog server address

fields.name: Port
fields.description: Syslog server port

fields.name: Network
fields.description: Network for syslog communication options: tcp, udp

fields.name: Protocol
fields.description: Protocol of syslog messages options: rfc5424, rfc3164

fields.name: EnableOctetCounting
fields.description: Whether or not to enable RFC 6587 Octet Counting.

fields.name: TLSSetting
fields.description: TLSSetting struct exposes TLS client configuration.
